<p>Mick’s key strength is rooted in his ability to communicate effectively with all manner of technical and engineering specialists, operational staff, and business owners, translating their knowledge and expectations into meaningful and productive systems. He joined Nevo in 2011 from Conservation Services Group (CSG), a leading energy services company providing program management, systems, and strategies for delivering high-volume energy efficiency and renewable energy programs.</p>
<p>At CSG he spent 15+ years defining the vision and requirements for, and leading the team that built complex engineering, analytical, and workflow software. He designed and constructed the core information systems, managed the software development department, and drove the software strategic vision as the company grew from 40 to over 850 people. Starting in the mid 1990’s, Mick developed one of the first mobile field energy analysis applications, with custom data synchronization to an enterprise-grade CRM, call center, and production/project management system that still manages CSG’s large residential energy efficiency business. Most recently, Mick led the team that drove the business requirements for the development of a next-generation residential energy analysis online/in-field application that Nevo built. Prior to working at CSG, Mick developed systems and analytic models at Eastern Research Group, primarily for the Environmental Protection Agency.</p>
<p>Mick’s unique combination of engineering, software development, and business experience evolved from a Bachelor’s degree in Mechanical Engineering from University College London, and he came to the US in 1990 on a Kennedy Scholarship to do a Masters in Technology and Public Policy at MIT.</p>
